detailResultFields.label: Course Section Definition Public Notes
detailResultFields.value:
This course is part of the Coordinated Arts Program, Individual & Society stream,  
https://cap.arts.ubc.ca/streams/individual-society/. Students must register in both Term
1 and Term 2 courses in CAP.

Please register in the lecture, and one of the following discussion sections: ECON_V 102-L8A, or ECON_V 102-L8B. This course is also clustered with PSYC_V 102-003, and the Individual & Society sections of the stream seminar CAP_V 101. For CAP_V 101, please select one of the following: CAP_V 101-I01, CAP_V 101-I02, CAP_V 101-I03, or CAP_V 101-I05. Follow the prompts to register in all stream seminars (1), lectures (2), and tutorials (1-2)each term.

For step-by-step instructions, please visit: https://cap.arts.ubc.ca/program/registration/

If you encounter any issues with registration into CAP, please contact us at support.fyip@ubc.ca

detailResultFields.label: Course Section Definition Public Notes
detailResultFields.value:
This course is part of the Coordinated Arts Program, Political Science, Philosophy and  Economics stream, https://cap.arts.ubc.ca/streams/political-science-philosophy-economics-ppe/. Students must register in both Term 1 and Term 2 courses in CAP.

In addition to the lecture, please register in one of the following discussion sections: ECON_V 102-L9A, or ECON_V 102-L9B. This course is also clustered with POLI_V 101-227, and PHIL_V 102-003. For POLI_V 101-227, please register in both the lecture, and one of the following discussion sections: POLI_V 101-LX1, POLI_V 101-LX2, POLI_V 101-LX3, POLI_V 101-LX4, POLI_V 101-LX5, or POLI_V 101-LX6. For PHIL_V 102-003, please register in both the lecture, and the discussion section PHIL_V 102-L07. Follow the prompts to register in all stream seminars (1), lectures (2), and tutorials (1-2)each term.

For step-by-step instructions, please visit: https://cap.arts.ubc.ca/program/registration/


If you encounter any issues with registration into CAP, please contact us at support.fyip@ubc.ca
